      • INSERT_INTO_COUPON

        public static java.lang.String INSERT_INTO_COUPON()
        The string that represents prepared SQL statement to insert Coupon object into the coupon table. SQL statement is: 
        INSERT INTO coupon 
 (TITLE, START_DATE, END_DATE, AMOUNT, TYPE, MESSAGE, PRICE, IMAGE) 
 VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)
        where first ? - is the title of current Coupon object, second ? - is the date when current Coupon object was created, third ? - is the date when current Coupon object will expire, forth ? - is the amount of current Coupon object in the stock, fifth ? - is the type of current Coupon object, sixth ? - is the message of current Coupon object, seventh ? - is the price of the current Coupon object, eighth ? - is the image of current Coupon object.
        Returns:
        String represents SQL INSERT statement.

      • UPDATE_COUPON

        public static java.lang.String UPDATE_COUPON()
        The string that represents prepared SQL statement to apply changes to already exists coupon in coupon table by id. SQL statement is: 
        UPDATE coupon SET END_DATE = ?, PRICE = ? WHERE ID = ?
        where first ? - is the date when current coupon will expire, second ? - is the price of the current coupon, third ? - is id of the current coupon.

        String represents SQL UPDATE statement.
